c145-001.frontera(1001)$ export OMP_NUM_THREADS='{0,2,4,6,8,10,12}:4:14,{1,3,5,7,9,11,13}:4:14}'
c145-001.frontera(1002)$ export OMP_NUM_THREADS=8
c145-001.frontera(1003)$ amask_omp -w20

     Each row of matrix is a mask for a Hardware Thread (hwt).
     CORE ID  = matrix digit + column group # in |...|
     A set mask bit (proc-id) = core id + add 56 to each additional row.

thrd |    0    |   10    |   20    |   30    |   40    |   50    |
0000 0-2-4-6-8-0-2-------------------------------------------
0001 --------------4-6-8-0-2-4-6-----------------------------
0002 ----------------------------8-0-2-4-6-8-0---------------
0003 ------------------------------------------2-4-6-8-0-2-4-
0004 -1-3-5-7-9-1-3------------------------------------------
0005 ---------------5-7-9-1-3-5-7----------------------------
0006 -----------------------------9-1-3-5-7-9-1--------------
0007 -------------------------------------------3-5-7-9-1-3-5
c145-001.frontera(1004)$ export OMP_NUM_THREADS=16
